                            <comment id="170027" author="adilger" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2016 23:23:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would also be useful to know why this test has started failing more often recently?  It has failed 7x in the past 2 days but only 23x in the past 6 weeks.  Is this fallout from some other patch that landed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="169799" author="adilger" created="Fri, 14 Oct 2016 22:54:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be good to fix the readahead algorithm to handle backward reads, including backward strides.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, DDN presented at LAD about improving the readahead code (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.eofs.eu/_media/events/lad16/19_parallel_readahead_framework_li_xi.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.eofs.eu/_media/events/lad16/19_parallel_readahead_framework_li_xi.pdf&lt;/a&gt;), and I believe that this also handled backward readahead, so if that will be available for 2.10 then we should use that instead of investing time into improving the existing readahead code to do this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
